<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8">
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
  <link rel="icon" href="/images/pp.jpg" type="image/x-icon">
  <link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.googleapis.com">
  <link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.gstatic.com" crossorigin>
  <link href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Merienda:wght@300..900&display=swap" rel="stylesheet">
  <title>The M's Hub - Fitness</title>
  <link rel="stylesheet" href="/styles/style.css">
  <style>
    @media screen and (max-width: 500px) {
      .card {
        width: 100%;
      }
      header {
        padding: 10px;
      }
      .profile h1 {
        font-size: 1.5em;
      }
      .profile h2 {
        font-size: 1em;
      }
      .nav ul li {
        margin-right: 10px;
      }
    }

    .fitness {
      position: relative;
      overflow: hidden;
      padding: 100px 0;
      text-align: center;
      color: #000;
      font-size: 18px;
    }

    .fitness::before {
      content: "";
      position: absolute;
      top: 0;
      left: 0;
      width: 100%;
      height: 100%;
      border-radius: 30px;
      background-color: aliceblue;
      background-size: cover;
      background-position: center;
      filter: blur(35px);
      opacity: 1.7;
      z-index: -1;
    }

    .fitness h2 {
      margin-bottom: 20px;
      font-size: 28px;
    }

    .fitness h3 {
      margin-bottom: 10px;
      font-size: 24px;
    }

    .fitness ul {
      list-style: none;
      padding: 0;
    }

    .fitness li {
      margin-bottom: 10px;
    }

    .fitness button {
      margin-top: 20px;
      padding: 10px 20px;
      font-size: 16px;
      background-color: #3498db;
      color: #fff;
      border: none;
      border-radius: 5px;
      cursor: pointer;
      transition: background-color 0.3s ease;
    }

    .fitness button:hover {
      background-color: #2980b9;
    }

    .fitness video {
      margin-bottom: 20px;
      max-width: 100%;
      cursor: pointer;
    }

    .fitness section {
      margin-bottom: 40px;
    }

    footer {
      padding: 20px;
      background-color: #333;
      color: #fff;
      text-align: center;
    }

    video {
      width: 50%;
    }

    .slide {
      background-color: lightblue;
      border-radius: 50px;
    }

    .card {
      background-color: aliceblue;
      color: black;
    }

    img {
      max-width: 100%;
      height: auto;
    }

    /* Modal Styles */
    .modal {
      display: none;
      position: fixed;
      z-index: 9999;
      padding-top: 60px;
      left: 0;
      top: 0;
      width: 100%;
      height: 100%;
      overflow: auto;
      background-color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.9);
    }

    .modal video {
      display: block;
      margin: auto;
      max-width: 90%;
      max-height: 80vh;
    }

    .modal .close {
      position: absolute;
      top: 20px;
      right: 35px;
      color: #fff;
      font-size: 40px;
      font-weight: bold;
      cursor: pointer;
    }
  </style>
</head>
<body>
  <%- include('partials/navbar') %>
  <div class="fitness">
    <section id="sales"></section>

    <section class="slide" id="home-workouts">
      <h2>Home Workouts (Bodyweight)</h2>
      <p>For most people, at-home solo workouts mean bodyweight-only exercises rather than studio classes and gym sessions that call for weights and other gear.</p>
      <p>Bodyweight workouts can be highly effective. They challenge your form, offering opportunities for improvement without needing gear or ample space. Below are insights into top bodyweight exercises for a comprehensive strength training regimen at home.</p>

      <div id="prefers">
        <h3>I Prefer </h3>
        <h1>AIR SQUATS</h1>
        <video autoplay loop playsinline muted aria-label="squat" src="/videos/squat.mp4"></video>
        <div class="card">
          <h2>Steps</h2>
          <p><strong>Step 1:</strong> Stand with feet shoulder-width apart. Lower your hips downward and backward, as if sitting in a chair.</p>
          <p><strong>Step 2:</strong> Push through your feet to rise back to a standing position. Keep weight centered in your heels.</p>
        </div>

        <h1>PUSH-UPS</h1>
        <video autoplay loop playsinline muted aria-label="pushup" src="/videos/pushups.mp4"></video>
        <div class="card">
          <h2>Steps</h2>
          <p><strong>Step 1:</strong> Assume a plank position with shoulders above wrists. Engage core.</p>
          <p><strong>Step 2:</strong> Lower body by bending elbows at a 45-degree angle.</p>
        </div>

        <h1>BURPEES</h1>
        <video autoplay loop playsinline muted aria-label="burpee" src="/videos/burpee.mp4"></video>
        <div class="card">
          <h2>Steps</h2>
          <p><strong>Step 1:</strong> Squat down, place hands on the ground, and jump feet back to a push-up position.</p>
          <p><strong>Step 2:</strong> Push up, jump forward, then jump and clap overhead.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div id="advantages">
        <h3>Advantages</h3>
        <ul>
          <li>Convenience and accessibility</li>
          <li>No need for expensive equipment</li>
          <li>Can be done anytime, anywhere</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
      <div id="disadvantages">
        <h3>Disadvantages</h3>
        <ul>
          <li>Limited variety of exercises</li>
          <li>Potential lack of motivation without a gym environment</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
      <p>Bodyweight workouts are cost-effective, versatile, and target all major muscle groups. They can be tailored to suit any fitness level. Whether you're looking to intensify or modify your routine, consider adding these exercises to your next home workout session.</p>
    </section>

    <section id="weight-training">
      <h2>Weight Training (Gym)</h2>
      <p>Find a trainer who specializes in weight training and has experience with clients at your fitness level. They can create personalized workout plans, teach proper techniques, and provide guidance on nutrition and recovery.</p>
      <div id="advantages">
        <h3>Advantages</h3>
        <ul>
          <li>Allows for progressive overload</li>
          <li>Can target specific muscle groups effectively</li>
          <li>Access to a wide range of equipment</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
      <div id="disadvantages">
        <h3>Disadvantages</h3>
        <ul>
          <li>Requires a gym membership or access to equipment</li>
          <li>Potential risk of injury if not done with proper form</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </section>
  </div>

  <!-- Video Modal -->
  <div id="videoModal" class="modal">
    <span class="close">&times;</span>
    <video id="modalVideo" controls autoplay></video>
  </div>

  <%- include('partials/footer') %>

  <script>
    document.querySelectorAll('.fitness video').forEach(video => {
      video.addEventListener('click', function () {
        const modal = document.getElementById("videoModal");
        const modalVideo = document.getElementById("modalVideo");

        modal.style.display = "block";
        modalVideo.src = this.src;
        modalVideo.play();
      });
    });

    document.querySelector('.modal .close').addEventListener('click', () => {
      const modal = document.getElementById("videoModal");
      const modalVideo = document.getElementById("modalVideo");

      modal.style.display = "none";
      modalVideo.pause();
      modalVideo.src = "";
    });

    window.addEventListener('click', (event) => {
      const modal = document.getElementById("videoModal");
      const modalVideo = document.getElementById("modalVideo");

      if (event.target == modal) {
        modal.style.display = "none";
        modalVideo.pause();
        modalVideo.src = "";
      }
    });
  </script>
</body>
</html>
